**Reasoning transparency** is a term used by the [Open Philanthropy Project]() to mean the degree to which a document is easy to interpret for the reader. Features that make a document easier to interpret include having key takeaways listed at the top, indicating which considerations are most important for the conclusion, expressing degrees of confidence for different statements made in the document, and so forth.

[Original page](https://www.openphilanthropy.org/reasoning-transparency).
